{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775831266650,"sessionID":"ses_288377134ffeKzs7TEfRaRN4QJ","part":{"id":"prt_d77c89a70001iw8QHOygaviXgC","messageID":"msg_d77c88fa2001khwDULlW3lGbQn","sessionID":"ses_288377134ffeKzs7TEfRaRN4QJ","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_fd8855d0ef39416b92136fd0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure to understand:\n1. The overall project layout and architecture\n2. The pkg/router directory contents and existing code patterns\n3. Any existing authentication/JWT related code\n4. Testing patterns used in the project\n5. Any existing design documents or specs related to ST-3 or AR-011\n\nSearch thoroughly in the current working directory and report back:\n- Directory structure (especially pkg/router/)\n- Existing router code patterns and conventions\n- Any JWT or auth related code\n- Test file patterns and frameworks used\n- Any relevant configuration files (go.mod, etc.)\n- Any design docs or specs mentioning ST-3 or AR-011\n\nReturn all findings in detail.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_288375301ffeI0ogwh0BcObDBr (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is my detailed report:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project Structure -- Comprehensive Analysis\n\n### 1. Overall Project Layout and Architecture\n\n**Project Root:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z`\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (Go 1.25.0)\n\n**Purpose:** AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n**Top-Level Directory Structure:**\n```\n.\n|-- changes/                  # AR (Architecture Request) change folders (AR-001 through AR-011)\n|-- ci-cd/                    # CI/CD design and spec\n|-- cli-toolkit/              # CLI design and spec\n|-- client-go/                # Generated Kubernetes client-go library\n|-- code-execution/           # Code execution design and spec\n|-- coverage.out              # Test coverage output\n|-- delta-spec.md             # Delta specification\n|-- deployment/               # Deployment design and spec\n|-- design.md                 # AR-011 design document (top-level copy)\n|-- go.mod / go.sum           # Go module files\n|-- idle-cleanup/             # Idle cleanup design and spec\n|-- integrations/             # Integration design and spec\n|-- pkg/                      # Core Go packages\n|-- project.md                # Project context document\n|-- proposal.md               # AR-011 proposal (top-level copy)\n|-- python-sdk/               # Python SDK design and spec\n|-- sandbox-orchestration/    # Sandbox orchestration design and spec\n|-- session-routing/          # Session routing design and spec\n|-- session-store/            # Session store design and spec\n|-- test_spec.md              # Test case specification (TDD)\n|-- testing/                  # TDD manifest\n|-- .sdd_prompt.md            # SDD prompt file\n```\n\n**pkg/ Directory Structure:**\n```\npkg/\n|-- apis/runtime/v1alpha1/    # Kubernetes CRD type definitions\n|-- common/types/             # Shared type aliases\n|-- router/                   # HTTP router/proxy (12 files)\n|-- store/                    # Session storage (Redis/Valkey)\n|-- workloadmanager/          # Workload management (handlers, reconciler, response)\n```\n\n**Architecture Flow:**\n```\nClient / SDK / CLI\n  -> Router (Deployment :8080)\n     <-> Redis/Valkey (session store)\n     -> WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n        <-> Redis/Valkey\n        -> K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n  Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n  Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. pkg/router Directory Contents and Code Patterns\n\n**Files in pkg/router/ (12 files):**\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `backend.go` | 92 | Backend struct, health checker with consecutive fail/success thresholds |\n| `config.go` | 32 | Server configuration (port, TLS, concurrency, session timeouts, store type) |\n| `errors.go` | 45 | Custom error types: `SessionNotFoundError`, `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError`, `SessionTerminatedError` |\n| `health.go` | 18 | Health check handlers (`/health/live`, `/health/ready`) |\n| `informer.go` | 84 | Kubernetes informer manager for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs |\n| `jwt.go` | 129 | JWTManager: RSA key generation, token signing (RS256), K8s Secret persistence |\n| `loadbalancer.go` | 100 | Load balancer interface with RoundRobin and LeastConnections implementations |\n| `middleware.go` | 55 | Gin middleware: ConcurrencyLimit, RequestLogger, TraceID |\n| `proxy.go` | 192 | Reverse proxy logic, session resolution, JWT injection to sandbox |\n| `router.go` | 79 | Basic Router interface and implementation (map-based routing) |\n| `server.go` | 139 | HTTP server setup, route registration, graceful shutdown |\n| `session_manager.go` | 176 | SessionManager interface and implementation (store + workload manager integration) |\n\n**Code Patterns and Conventions:**\n\n1. **Package naming:** Single package `router`, all files in `package router`\n2. **Interface-first design:** `Router`, `LoadBalancer`, `SessionManager`, `Store` are all interfaces\n3. **Constructor pattern:** `NewXxx()` functions returning interfaces or concrete types with error\n4. **Gin framework:** Uses `gin-gonic/gin` for HTTP routing with middleware chain\n5. **Error handling:** Custom typed errors with `Error()` method; HTTP error responses as `gin.H{\"error\": \"...\", \"code\": \"...\"}`\n6. **Logging:** Uses `k8s.io/klog/v2` for structured logging (no `log.Printf`)\n7. **Concurrency:** `sync.RWMutex` for route maps, `sync.Mutex` for health checkers, atomic counters for load balancer\n8. **Configuration:** `Config` struct with `NewDefaultConfig()` factory\n9. **Reverse proxy:** Uses `net/http/httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy` with custom `Director` and `ErrorHandler`\n\n**Route Registration Pattern (server.go):**\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) registerRoutes() {\n    s.engine.GET(\"/health/live\", handleHealthLive)\n    s.engine.GET(\"/health/ready\", s.handleHealthReady)\n\n    v1 := s.engine.Group(\"/v1\")\n    v1.Use(gin.Logger())\n    v1.Use(gin.Recovery())\n    v1.Use(ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(s.config.MaxConcurrentRequests))\n\n    v1.GET(\"/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleAgentInvoke)\n    v1.POST(\"/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleAgentInvoke)\n    v1.GET(\"/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleCodeInterpreterInvoke)\n    v1.POST(\"/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleCodeInterpreterInvoke)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Authentication/JWT Related Code\n\n**File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`** -- Current JWT capabilities:\n\n- **JWTManager struct:**\n  ```go\n  type JWTManager struct {\n      privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n      publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n      clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **Constants:**\n  - `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n  - `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n  - `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n  - `PrivateKeyDataKey = \"private.pem\"`\n  - `PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"`\n  - `IdentityNamespace = \"default\"` (overridable via `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var)\n\n- **Current methods:**\n  - `NewJWTManager()` -- generates RSA 2048 key pair\n  - `GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)` -- signs with RS256, base claims: `exp`, `iat`, `iss: \"agentcube-router\"`\n  - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` -- persists/loads keys from K8s Secret\n  - `loadPrivateKeyPEM(data []byte)` -- loads private key from PEM\n\n- **Outbound JWT injection (proxy.go):** In `forwardToSandbox`, when kind is `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim`, generates JWT and sets `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on proxied request.\n\n- **What is MISSING (per AR-011):**\n  - `PublicKey()` accessor method\n  - `ParseAndValidateToken(tokenString string)` for inbound verification\n  - `AuthMiddleware` gin middleware\n  - JWT-related config fields (`JWTExpiration`, `JWTIssuer`, `JWTLeeway`)\n  - Registration of AuthMiddleware on `/v1` routes\n\n---\n\n### 4. Testing Patterns Used in the Project\n\n**Test Framework:** Standard Go `testing` package + `github.com/stretchr/testify` (assert, require)\n\n**Test File Locations (9 existing test files):**\n```\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type_test.go\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types_test.go\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/constants_test.go\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info_test.go\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types_test.go\npkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_delete_test.go\npkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_lifecycle_test.go\npkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics_test.go\npkg/workloadmanager/response/response_test.go\n```\n\n**Testing Patterns Observed:**\n\n1. **Table-driven tests:** Using `[]struct{}` with `t.Run()` for boundary conditions\n2. **Gin test context:** `gin.CreateTestContext(httptest.NewRecorder())` for handler testing\n3. **Mock stores:** `newMockStore()` for in-memory store simulation\n4. **Fake K8s clients:** `fake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)` for Kubernetes client mocking\n5. **HTTP recorder:** `httptest.NewRecorder()` for capturing HTTP responses\n6. **Assertion style:** `assert.Equal`, `assert.NoError`, `assert.Error`, `assert.Contains`, `require.NoError`\n7. **Test naming:** `TestStructName_MethodName_Scenario` convention (e.g., `TestLifecycleManager_IsExpired_BoundaryConditions`)\n\n**Example test pattern (from sandbox_lifecycle_test.go):**\n```go\nfunc TestLifecycleManager_GetSandboxStatus_Success(t *testing.T) {\n    gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\n    w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    c, _ := gin.CreateTestContext(w)\n    c.Request = httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, \"/status/session-123\", nil)\n    c.Params = gin.Params{{Key: \"sessionID\", Value: \"session-123\"}}\n\n    store := newMockStore()\n    // ... setup ...\n    mgr := NewLifecycleManager(&LifecycleManagerDeps{Store: store})\n    mgr.GetSandboxStatus(c)\n\n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, w.Code)\n    // ... response validation ...\n}\n```\n\n**TDD Requirements (from testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md):**\n- **Test-RT-1:** Construct invalid JWT, verify 401 Unauthorized\n- **Test-RT-2:** Construct expired JWT, verify \"Token Expired\" response\n- **Test-RT-3:** Simulate backend timeout, verify Gateway Timeout handling\n- **Test-RT-4:** Verify header passthrough (Host, X-Forwarded-For, etc.)\n- **T/C Ratio:** Must be > 0.4 (test lines / code lines)\n- **Every `*.go` file must have a corresponding `*_test.go` file**\n\n**Current gap:** `pkg/router/` has NO test files yet. All router code is untested.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Design Documents and Specs Related to ST-3 and AR-011\n\n**ST-3 References:**\nST-3 refers to \"Design Complete\" stage. The following ARs are marked at ST-3:\n- AR-002, AR-004, AR-005, AR-006, AR-007, AR-009 (all in `changes/AR-XXX/tasks.md`)\n\n**AR-011 Documents (Router JWT Authentication and Signing):**\n\n| File | Path | Status |\n|------|------|--------|\n| **Proposal** | `changes/AR-011/proposal.md` | Stage: ST-1 (Proposal), mostly TODO placeholders |\n| **Design** | `changes/AR-011/design.md` | Mostly TODO placeholders |\n| **Delta Spec** | `changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md` | **Fully detailed** -- 345 lines of Gherkin-style requirements |\n| **Tasks** | `changes/AR-011/tasks.md` | Stage: ST-1, mostly TODO placeholders |\n\nThere are also top-level copies:\n- `/design.md` -- Full AR-011 design (638 lines, detailed)\n- `/proposal.md` -- AR-011 proposal (218 lines, detailed)\n\n**Key AR-011 Requirements (from delta-spec.md):**\n\n1. **JWTManager.PublicKey()** -- Return RSA public key accessor\n2. **JWTManager.ParseAndValidateToken()** -- Inbound JWT validation with RS256, exp/iat/iss checks, 1-minute leeway\n3. **AuthMiddleware(jwtManager)** -- Gin middleware for Bearer token authentication\n4. **Route registration** -- Add AuthMiddleware to `/v1` group (after Recovery, before ConcurrencyLimit)\n5. **Health endpoints public** -- `/health/*` must remain unauthenticated\n6. **Outbound signing unchanged** -- Existing proxy.go JWT injection preserved\n7. **Config extension** -- `JWTExpiration`, `JWTIssuer`, `JWTLeeway` fields\n8. **JWTConfig struct** -- `NewJWTManager(config *JWTConfig)` with nil-default behavior\n9. **Build/test gates** -- `go build`, `go test -v`, `go test -race`, T/C > 0.4, no `log.Printf`\n\n**Error response format:**\n| Error | HTTP | Body |\n|-------|------|------|\n| Missing Auth header | 401 | `{\"error\": \"missing authorization header\", \"code\": \"UNAUTHORIZED\"}` |\n| Invalid format | 401 | `{\"error\": \"invalid authorization format\", \"code\": \"UNAUTHORIZED\"}` |\n| Token expired | 401 | `{\"error\": \"token is expired\", \"code\": \"TOKEN_EXPIRED\"}` |\n| Invalid signature | 401 | `{\"error\": \"invalid token\", \"code\": \"UNAUTHORIZED\"}` |\n\n---\n\n### 6. Key Configuration Files\n\n**go.mod:**\n```\nmodule github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\ngo 1.25.0\n\nKey dependencies:\n- github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0\n- github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.1\n- github.com/google/uuid v1.6.0\n- github.com/stretchr/testify v1.11.1\n- k8s.io/api v0.34.1\n- k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1\n- k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1\n- sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.22.2\n- github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.18.0\n- github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.73\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **pkg/router/ has 12 Go source files but ZERO test files** -- all `*_test.go` files need to be created\n2. **JWT code exists but is outbound-only** -- `jwt.go` has key generation and signing, but no validation/verification\n3. **AR-011 delta-spec.md is the authoritative requirements document** -- it has 17 detailed Gherkin scenarios\n4. **The top-level design.md and proposal.md are far more complete** than the copies in `changes/AR-011/`\n5. **Testing pattern is well-established** in `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/` -- use gin test context, mock stores, testify assertions\n6. **Middleware chain order matters** -- AuthMiddleware must go after Recovery but before ConcurrencyLimit\n7. **Health endpoints must remain public** -- they are registered outside the `/v1` group\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288375301ffeI0ogwh0BcObDBr","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775831133435,"end":1775831266648}}}}
